with open("../data/resources/rcParams.yaml") as f:
    rcParamsDict = yaml.full_load(f)
    for k in rcParamsDict["rcParams"]:
        print("{} {}".format(k,rcParamsDict["rcParams"][k]))
        plt.rcParams[k] = rcParamsDict["rcParams"][k]
    for k1 in set(list(rcParamsDict)).difference(set(["rcParams"])):
        print("{} {}".format(k1,rcParamsDict[k1]))

sc.pp.calculate_qc_metrics(runs_dict["sample1"], log1p=True, inplace=False)
    
#Find mito and ribo genes
mito_genes = runs_dict["sample1"].var_names.str.startswith("MT-")   
ribo_genes = runs_dict["sample1"].var_names.str.contains("^RPS|^RPL")

#qc_vars wants a column of adata.var containing T/F or 1/0 indicating the genes to be selected for sub-statistics
runs_dict["sample1"].var["mito"] = runs_dict["sample1"].var_names.str.startswith("MT-")    
runs_dict["sample1"].var["ribo"]= runs_dict["sample1"].var_names.str.contains("^RPS|^RPL")

#Compute metrics (inplace=True to append to adata)
sc.pp.calculate_qc_metrics(runs_dict["sample1"], log1p=True, qc_vars=["mito","ribo"], inplace=True, percent_top=None)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize = (20, 4), gridspec_kw = dict(wspace = 0.4))
axs = axs.flatten().T

for ax, meta in zip(axs, ["total_counts", "n_genes_by_counts", "pct_counts_mito"]):

    sc.pl.violin(runs_dict["sample1"], keys=meta, jitter=0, multi_panel=True, rotation = 45, groupby = "Consensus", 
                ax = ax, show = False, palette = lines_palette)

    ax.set_xticklabels(np.unique(runs_dict["sample1"].obs["Consensus"]), rotation = 60, rotation_mode="anchor", ha="right")

plt.show()
